Installation:

    git clone git@github.com:JochenHeizmann/dotvim.git ~/.vim

Create symlinks:

    ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
    ln -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc

Switch to the `~/.vim` directory, and fetch submodules:

    cd ~/.vim
    git submodule init
    git submodule update

When you start VIM for the first time, the following plugins will be installed automatically (thanks to vim-addon-manager):

    * FuzzyFinder
    * L9
    * MRU
    * The_NERD_tree
    * snipMate
    * tComment
    * taglist
    * tlib
    * vim-addon-actions
    * vim-addon-background-cmd
    * vim-addon-completion
    * vim-addon-goto-thing-at-cursor
    * vim-addon-manager-known-repositories
    * vim-addon-mw-utils
    * vim-addon-swfmill
    * vim-addon-views
    * vim-haxe
    * xmledit
